---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const calendlyUrl = 'https://calendly.com/jake-qmqx/right-fit-call';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Margin Theory CFO Services | Fractional CFO for $1M to $20M owner-operators"
  description="The fractional CFO practice behind Margin Theory. Monthly rhythm for owner-operator businesses doing $1M to $20M. We trace the money five drivers down."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section>
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-20 md:pt-32 md:pb-28">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-6">CFO Services</div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-[1.05] mb-6">
            Get a financial guide who sees what you can't.
          </h1>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-white/80 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            Get a fractional CFO who traces the money five drivers down, finds what's hiding in your own business, and builds the financial operating system that lets you see further. All for one flat monthly fee.
          </p>
          <a
            href={calendlyUrl}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-margin-blue text-white font-semibold rounded-md hover:opacity-90 transition"
          >
            Schedule a Right Fit Call
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="hidden md:flex items-center justify-center">
          <div class="w-full aspect-square rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] flex items-center justify-center">
            <div class="text-center px-8">
              <div class="text-6xl font-bold text-margin-blue mb-2">$110K</div>
              <div class="text-lg text-white/60">per month recovered</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-white/40 mt-1">RDM Hospitality. Don Julio.</div>
              <div class="w-16 h-px bg-margin-blue/40 mx-auto my-4"></div>
              <div class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">The data was sitting in the business the whole time. Someone had to pop the hood.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Does This Sound Like You? -->
  <section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">The problem</div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8">Does this sound like you?</h2>
          <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <span class="text-margin-blue text-2xl leading-none mt-1">·</span>
              <p><span class="text-white font-semibold">Your business relies on you, or it all falls apart.</span> You built it with your hands and your gut. Now it's too big for either.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <span class="text-margin-blue text-2xl leading-none mt-1">·</span>
              <p><span class="text-white font-semibold">You're stuck in a Catch-22.</span> You need to grow to hire, but you need to hire to grow. Cash is always tight at the wrong moment.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <span class="text-margin-blue text-2xl leading-none mt-1">·</span>
              <p><span class="text-white font-semibold">You don't have a simple way to know what's working.</span> Your accountant sends reports months late. By then the money already leaked.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <span class="text-margin-blue text-2xl leading-none mt-1">·</span>
              <p><span class="text-white font-semibold">You know the business has more in it.</span> You just can't see where the money is hiding or what lever to pull next.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <div class="p-8 border border-margin-blue/30 rounded-xl bg-margin-blue/[0.03] w-full">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">The business owner's trap:</div>
            <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              You're an expert at your craft. You're not an expert at running the financial side of a business. Nobody taught you that part.
            </p>
            <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              So six figures hides in your P&L every year, one layer below where anyone is looking. In the COGS detail. In the cash-vs-accrual gap. In the timing of payroll and AR.
            </p>
            <p class="text-margin-blue font-semibold text-lg">
              That's the margin. And most operators never find it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What's a Fractional CFO? -->
  <section class="border-t border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">The solution</div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">What's a fractional CFO?</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              A CFO's job is to guide a business toward more profit, more cash flow, and better decisions. A fractional CFO does the same thing, but for businesses that don't need (or can't afford) a full-time hire at $200K+ per year.
            </p>
            <p>
              You get the strategic financial brain without the full-time salary. Monthly working sessions. A live forecast. A KPI dashboard that actually means something. And a 30-day action plan after every session.
            </p>
            <p class="text-white font-semibold">
              One flat fee per month. No hourly billing. No surprises.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <div class="text-margin-blue font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Not a bookkeeper</div>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Your bookkeeper records what happened. Your CFO tells you what to do about it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <div class="text-margin-blue font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Not a tax accountant</div>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Your CPA files the return. Your CFO makes sure the numbers on that return are as good as they can be.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <div class="text-margin-blue font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Not a business coach</div>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">A coach gives you frameworks. Your CFO gives you the actual numbers and tells you exactly where the money is.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Your CFO Will Do -->
  <section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">The deliverables</div>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">What your CFO will do for you.</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/60 mb-12 max-w-3xl">Every month, you get three things that transform how you operate.</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
        <div class="p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-margin-blue text-4xl font-bold mb-4">01</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">A Scoreboard</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
            Track your profit and cash flow every month. See the 3 to 5 KPIs that actually move your business. Know exactly where you stand, updated weekly.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-margin-blue text-4xl font-bold mb-4">02</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">An Action Plan</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
            After every monthly session, you leave with a prioritized 30-day action plan. What to do, in what order, with dollar amounts attached to each move.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-margin-blue text-4xl font-bold mb-4">03</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">A Financial Guide</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
            Between calls, you have a CFO in your corner. When an urgent decision hits, we model it in the forecast within 24 hours and come back with a recommendation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center">
        <a
          href={calendlyUrl}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-margin-blue text-white font-semibold rounded-md hover:opacity-90 transition"
        >
          Schedule a Right Fit Call
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Makes Us Different -->
  <section class="border-t border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">The difference</div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8">What makes Margin Theory different.</h2>
          <div class="space-y-8 text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-xl mb-2">We go five drivers down.</h3>
              <p>
                Most fractional CFOs stop at "COGS is too high" or "labor is creeping up." Margin Theory keeps going. Which line? Which SKU? Which shift? Which person? That's where the real money is.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-xl mb-2">We understand the whole machine.</h3>
              <p>
                Unlike an accountant who sees the financials, or a coach who sees the strategy, we see both. We connect the operational decisions to their financial impact in real time.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-xl mb-2">Flat fee. No hourly billing.</h3>
              <p>
                You should never hesitate to call your CFO because a clock is running. One flat monthly fee. Use us as much as you need.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <div class="p-8 border-l-2 border-margin-blue bg-white/[0.02] rounded-r-xl w-full">
            <p class="text-xl text-white font-semibold leading-snug mb-4">
              "COGS high. Which line? Wine cost. Which SKU? Don Julio. What drove it? Over-pours and miscounts. Where? Two bartenders, two shifts."
            </p>
            <p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              That's five drivers down. That trace recovered $110,000 per month in cash flow at RDM Hospitality. The data was sitting in the business the whole time.
            </p>
            <p class="text-margin-blue font-semibold">
              Someone had to pop the hood.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Proof / Testimonials -->
  <section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">Proof</div>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-12">Real operators. Real results.</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-margin-blue text-3xl font-bold mb-1">$110K/mo</div>
          <div class="text-white/50 text-sm mb-4">recovered cash flow</div>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Beverage COGS traced five drivers down to specific SKUs, specific bartenders, specific shifts. The money was leaking every single day.
          </p>
          <div class="text-sm text-white/40">RDM Hospitality</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-margin-blue text-3xl font-bold mb-1">Cash forecast</div>
          <div class="text-white/50 text-sm mb-4">that changed everything</div>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Built a 12-month rolling cash forecast that turned weekly panic into weekly clarity. The founder could finally sleep at night.
          </p>
          <div class="text-sm text-white/40">Ultimis Construction</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-margin-blue text-3xl font-bold mb-1">Chemistry gap</div>
          <div class="text-white/50 text-sm mb-4">caught before close</div>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            An acquisition target's chemistry costs were hiding a margin problem the buyer couldn't see. We caught it in the detail. Saved the deal from becoming a disaster.
          </p>
          <div class="text-sm text-white/40">Car wash acquisition</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The 4 Pillars -->
  <section class="border-t border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">What you get</div>
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Four things every operator deserves.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="text-center p-6">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-margin-blue mb-4">1</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Complete Clarity</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Know your profitability, cash position, and the drivers behind both. No more guessing. No more waiting for reports that arrive too late.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-margin-blue mb-4">2</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Complete Guidance</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            A financial expert who has seen what works and what doesn't across dozens of businesses in your revenue range. Cuts your learning curve in half.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-margin-blue mb-4">3</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Complete Growth</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Every decision informed by real data. Not gut instinct at $3M. Real numbers, real forecasts, real clarity on which bets to make and which to pass on.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-margin-blue mb-4">4</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Complete Freedom</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Get your time back. Stop spending nights wondering if you can make payroll. Hand the financial worry to someone whose entire job is to carry it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About / Founder -->
  <section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">Your CFO</div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">Jake Erickson</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Fractional CFO for owner-operator businesses doing $1M to $20M. Built the Margin Theory method by finding money hiding in inventory counts, cash-vs-accrual gaps, and operator blind spots in businesses nobody else could see through.
            </p>
            <p>
              The work that built the brand: $110K per month recovered in beverage COGS at RDM Hospitality. The cash forecast that let Dan McCaulley sleep at night again. The car wash chemistry gap that saved a buyer from the outsider-buyer failure pattern.
            </p>
            <p>
              Margin Theory exists because every business between $1M and $20M produces the data it needs to double its performance. The answers are already inside. Someone has to be willing to trace them five drivers down.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center">
          <div class="w-full max-w-sm aspect-[3/4] rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] flex items-center justify-center">
            <div class="text-center px-8">
              <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-3">The mission</div>
              <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
                Help 10,000 owner-operators find the margin hiding in their own business. Increase profitability by 20%. Provide financial clarity every single month. Give founders back 100+ hours a year they're currently spending worrying about cash.
              </p>
              <div class="w-12 h-px bg-margin-blue/40 mx-auto my-4"></div>
              <p class="text-white/50 text-xs">Specializing in $1M to $20M owner-operator businesses</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Process -->
  <section class="border-t border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">The process</div>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">One clear path from hidden to obvious.</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/60 mb-12 max-w-3xl">
        Every engagement follows the same proven structure. Phase 1 makes the machine visible. Phase 2 reads the machine together, every month, and finds the money hiding five drivers down.
      </p>

      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full border border-margin-blue text-margin-blue text-sm font-bold">P1</span>
          Phase 1: Make the machine visible
          <span class="text-sm font-normal text-white/40 ml-2">First 30 days</span>
        </h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Financial Assessment</h4>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Books, P&L, balance sheet, cash position, AR, AP, payroll timing. We find where the business is right now and which drivers are moving the numbers.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Annual Profit & Cash Targets</h4>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Set the numbers the business is trying to hit for the year. Grounded in actual operating economics, not wishful thinking.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">12-Month Rolling Cash Forecast</h4>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Week-by-week cash position for the next 12 months, updated monthly. Tight weeks and cushion weeks, color coded.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">KPI Dashboard</h4>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">The 3 to 5 numbers that actually move the business. Not a vanity dashboard. Watched weekly. Tied to the financials.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">3 Opportunities, Dollar-Sized</h4>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">At least three specific ways to improve financial performance, each with an estimated dollar impact you can act on this quarter.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full border border-margin-blue text-margin-blue text-sm font-bold">P2</span>
          Phase 2: Read the machine together
          <span class="text-sm font-normal text-white/40 ml-2">Ongoing</span>
        </h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Monthly CFO Working Session</h4>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">90 minutes. Actuals vs. targets. The month's main constraint. A 30-day action plan with owners and deadlines.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Weekly Friday Check-In</h4>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Short accountability pulse on the 30-day plan. No formal report required. Just make sure the needle is moving.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Between-Call Decision Support</h4>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">When an urgent decision hits, we model it in the forecast within 24 hours and come back with a recommendation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Rolling Forecast & KPI Updates</h4>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">The forecast moves forward one month every month. The KPI dashboard refreshes with the latest actuals.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Right Fit Call -->
  <section class="border-t border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">Next step</div>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">Schedule a Right Fit Call.</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-10 text-left">
          <p>
            We may not be a right fit for you. That's fine. The Right Fit Call is 30 minutes and free. Here's what happens:
          </p>
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 py-4">
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-margin-blue mb-2">1</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/70">We look at your financials together and identify the 2 to 3 biggest problems.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-margin-blue mb-2">2</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/70">We explain how the CFO engagement works and what Phase 1 looks like for your business.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-margin-blue mb-2">3</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/70">We discuss the fee and you decide if it makes sense. No pressure. No follow-up sequence.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-center text-white/60">
            You'll leave the call knowing exactly where your money is hiding, whether we work together or not.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a
          href={calendlyUrl}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-margin-blue text-white text-lg font-semibold rounded-md hover:opacity-90 transition"
        >
          Schedule Your Right Fit Call
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
